The text of Propertius is notoriously in an unsatis- factory condition: amongst the texts os the great Roman poets there is none which presents difficulties so great. The comparative value of the existing MSS. of Pro pertius, and their mutual relation to each other, have not even yet been settled beyond dispute. Of these the first
